  "description": "Disaster Transport (originally Avalanche Run) was an enclosed steel bobsled roller coaster built by Intamin at Cedar Point in Sandusky, Ohio, United States.  It was notable as being the only indoor roller coaster at Cedar Point, the only bobsled roller coaster in the Midwestern United States, and the only enclosed bobsled roller coaster in the world at its debut.  The name of the ride stems from a rearrangement of the letters \"Dispatch Master Transport\", which could still be seen in the ride's logo in its later years.",
